rComments: On-point lecturer :), one of the best, interactive class discussions. Fair exams, recommend
Hope she stays next semester ! Great prof

I had Dr. Potvin-Kent for many of my HSS classes! The BEST prof in the Health of Sciences Bachelor, she's an amazing professor. Highly recommended, take any class she teaches. Her classes requires effort, reading, assignments, but very interesting! :) The work you put in is representative of your grade! She's very approchable and helpful!

I absolutely LOVE professor Potvin-Kent. She has reasonable expectations, so if you study hard you will get a good note. She is also very entertaining during her classes and she tries to make dull materiel interesting. I would take her for for all my classes if I could! Very sad to see her go next semester...

Interesting lectures. The material is not hard, but it is a cumulative final exam. 1 group project, witch was easy to get a good mark on (only 2 pages long).  The prof explains very well in the lectures.

Not sure why she has such a low rating! I'm assuming they're all from her french lectures (maybe she's not that great in french) but in English she gives AMAZING lectures I always look forward to her class, she doesn't read off the slides and she's engaging and interesting to listen to. One of my favourite profs!!

Dr Potvin-Kent is a pretty good prof, easy to do well if you do the readings and go to class. She does add her somewhat hypocritical views to certain topics and she can be condescending if you have an opposing view. Almost all random stats she says to memorize will be on tests, you can easily get a B+ by just attending class and reviewing slides.

It seems like the french version of this course was horrible! But I absolutely loved this class. Do you readings, go to class and you will get an A. Final was a little harder but study harder and you will do well.
All she does is read the notes from the powerpoints. Her grading is really tough, and subjective. Not a good teacher!

She's not a good teacher. She's a tough grader and she's not fair either with her grading. She's not a motivating teacher and she just reads the notes from the powerpoints most of the time. Avoid this teacher if you can.
Horrible teacher. All she does is read her notes and is horrible at translating to french. Not specific at all on what to expect on her exams. Avoid AT ALL COST you do DO NOT want her as a teacher.

Wonderful professor! She knows her stuff and her exams are not bad at all if you attend class and read the textbook. However, she uses way too many statistics and she should include her supplemental slides in the student version of the power points. Can't note down all that information in 30 seconds

She is a good professor and very nice. I really like her nutrition class, she knows what she is talking about.  If she tells you to memorize numbers, memorize them. She doesn't try trick people. Go to class because she gives extra information.  I don't know why people are saying bad  things about her, if you study and go to class you'll do good.

She's a very good prof and she clearly knows her stuff. There's a lot of stuff to remember and her final exam is cumulative. She is very unclear on what she expects from us but overall if you study absolutely everything by heart you should be fine. If you don't like group projects avoid, because there's a 15min group presentation you must do.
lol terrible prof

She's a good prof, knows her stuff. However, she does have the tendency to read off the slides.  She has that mentality to trick her students... She told a friend of mine that when she's teaching, if she notices that people aren't listening... she'll mark down what she talking about at that point and ask questions on that subject on the exam lol

She's a terrible prof. All she does is read her notes and give you statistics to learn by heart. Her exams are ONLY about little details, and she is very unclear about what you have to study. She also makes her french class buy an expensive English textbook. Avoid at all cost.

GET OUT!! she doesn't know what she's teaching, she reads the slides verbatim and only provides you with one sentence so you are spending your time writing out her notes the entire class. She wants everyone to do poorly on the first midterm so that it can be weighed out at the end. Very poor teaching skills and marking, go with another prof if you

she's so nice! definitely an easy class, just study her powerpoints and make sure to get her notes from class. she says she tests from the textbook but she actually doesn't, so just study the notes and it will be an easy A
Not a bad prof, she's really nice when you get to know her. Her class can get boring because all you do is copy notes. Quite easy to get an A if you study all the material.

Awesome prof! Yes the midterm was long and bell curved a lot but this was the first time the class was ever taught. I'm sure it will be better next year. She is really nice, enthusiastic and a great teacher. She even brought a yoga instructor in for a guest 'lecture'! Her exams are fair, and the class is a lot of fun. Thanks Dr. Potvin-Kent!
This professor was not meant to teach this course. She makes it hard for nothing. Had to bell curve midterm 27%. Stay away from her if you can.

Midterm was ridiculously long, but not necessarily difficult. But when you have to bell curve 27%., there's a problem though. Too much focus on nutrition aspect of health problems rather than actual disease states. Was bored during most lectures as she read from slides, and had to type all the notes she failed to post online. Not awful, not great.
